575
00:41:35,124 --> 00:41:37,058
Capone owns none of it.

576
00:41:37,126 --> 00:41:40,061
We can get him on income tax evasion

577
00:41:40,129 --> 00:41:43,064
if we can show that he's getting money

578
00:41:43,132 --> 00:41:44,429
from the organization's business.

579
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:47,628
See, legally he receives no income.

580
00:41:47,703 --> 00:41:49,136
He doesn't receive anything?

581
00:41:49,204 --> 00:41:50,136
[Knock Knock]

582
00:41:50,205 --> 00:41:52,639
Mr. Ness, you have a visitor.

583
00:41:52,708 --> 00:41:55,142
Mr. Ness, could we talk?

584
00:41:55,210 --> 00:41:56,905
John O'Shea, alderman.

585
00:41:56,979 --> 00:41:58,913
I know who you are.

586
00:42:01,350 --> 00:42:02,783
Would you excuse us?

587
00:42:05,654 --> 00:42:08,589
We have several large operations in the works.

588
00:42:08,657 --> 00:42:10,591
What can I do for you?

589
00:42:10,659 --> 00:42:13,093
I came up to congratulate you

590
00:42:13,162 --> 00:42:15,460
on a job well done,

591
00:42:15,531 --> 00:42:19,797
share your good fortune on such a lovely day.

592
00:42:23,439 --> 00:42:25,236
What's that?

593
00:42:29,612 --> 00:42:31,136
What is that?

594
00:42:31,213 --> 00:42:33,477
Mr. Ness, you're an educated man.

595
00:42:33,549 --> 00:42:36,541
Let me pay you the compliment of being blunt.

596
00:42:36,619 --> 00:42:38,109
There is a large,

597
00:42:38,187 --> 00:42:40,587
a large and popular business

598
00:42:40,656 --> 00:42:42,886
which you are causing dismay.

599
00:42:42,958 --> 00:42:45,893
Why don't you just cross the street

600
00:42:45,961 --> 00:42:48,395
and let things take their course?

601
00:42:48,464 --> 00:42:50,898
Would you come in here please?

602
00:42:55,804 --> 00:42:57,237
In Roman times,

603
00:42:57,306 --> 00:42:58,739
when a fella was convicted

604
00:42:58,807 --> 00:43:01,241
of trying to bribe a public official,

605
00:43:01,310 --> 00:43:05,246
they'd sew him in a bag with a wild animal

606
00:43:05,314 --> 00:43:07,748
and throw that bag in the river.

607
00:43:07,816 --> 00:43:09,147
You tell your master

608
00:43:09,218 --> 00:43:11,948
that we must agree to disagree.

609
00:43:13,589 --> 00:43:15,022
You're making a mistake.

610
00:43:15,090 --> 00:43:17,820
I've made them before.
I'm beginning to enjoy them.

611
00:43:17,893 --> 00:43:19,588
You're untouchable, is that it?

612
00:43:19,662 --> 00:43:21,220
No one can get to you?

613
00:43:21,296 --> 00:43:22,729
And you tell Capone...

614
00:43:22,798 --> 00:43:24,527
Everyone can be gotten to.

615
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,329
I'll see him in hell.

616
00:43:28,504 --> 00:43:29,937
Hey, nice house.

617
00:43:30,005 --> 00:43:31,836
I said nice house.

618
00:43:31,907 --> 00:43:33,340
You live there?

619
00:43:34,710 --> 00:43:37,235
Little girl's having a birthday, huh?

620
00:43:39,708 --> 00:43:40,732
Yes.

621
00:43:40,775 --> 00:43:43,073
Nice to have a family.

622
00:43:45,614 --> 00:43:47,104
Yes, it is.

623
00:43:48,483 --> 00:43:50,917
A man should take care,

624
00:43:50,986 --> 00:43:53,420
see that nothing happens to them.

625
00:44:08,036 --> 00:44:09,298
Katherine!

626
00:44:11,706 --> 00:44:13,037
Katherine!

627
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:14,541
Where's the baby?

628
00:44:14,609 --> 00:44:16,236
She's upstairs. Eliot...

629
00:44:18,380 --> 00:44:19,312
Ohh...

630
00:44:19,381 --> 00:44:20,313
Daddy.

631
00:44:23,285 --> 00:44:25,310
Ohh, yes.

632
00:44:28,790 --> 00:44:30,724
What were you doing up?

633
00:44:30,792 --> 00:44:32,726
I had to finish my ironing.

634
00:44:32,794 --> 00:44:33,818
You did?

635
00:44:35,130 --> 00:44:38,065
You're going to come with Daddy now, O.K.?

636
00:44:49,744 --> 00:44:50,870
Eliot.

637
00:44:50,946 --> 00:44:52,379
O.K., it's all right.

638
00:44:52,447 --> 00:44:54,312
O.K., let's go.

639
00:44:54,382 --> 00:44:55,610
Stay there!

640
00:44:55,684 --> 00:44:58,744
Keep your eye on the street.

641
00:45:00,355 --> 00:45:01,379
Where's Malone?

642
00:45:01,456 --> 00:45:04,391
He's on the stakeout.
He'll be right here.

643
00:45:04,459 --> 00:45:05,391
Who's he?

644
00:45:05,460 --> 00:45:08,588
One of the men on his list. He's O.K.

645
00:45:08,663 --> 00:45:11,598
All right, then.
Drive them to the station.

646
00:45:11,666 --> 00:45:14,601
She'll tell you where to go when you're there.

647
00:45:14,669 --> 00:45:16,102
Take off your hat.

648
00:45:16,171 --> 00:45:19,106
Anything happens, you shoot first,
you understand me?

649
00:45:19,174 --> 00:45:20,607
Yes, Mr. Ness.

650
00:45:25,447 --> 00:45:26,914
Kiss.

651
00:45:26,982 --> 00:45:28,711
Eskimo and butterfly, Dad.

652
00:45:28,783 --> 00:45:29,715
O.K.

653
00:45:33,188 --> 00:45:34,917
Now, go.

654
00:45:57,912 --> 00:45:59,812
Malone.

655
00:45:59,881 --> 00:46:01,314
Are you O.K.?

656
00:46:01,383 --> 00:46:04,318
They're fine.
Are you sure the cop's O.K.?

657
00:46:04,386 --> 00:46:06,820
He better be.
He's my cousin.

658
00:46:06,888 --> 00:46:08,822
I want to hurt the man.

659
00:46:08,890 --> 00:46:11,825
I want to start taking the battle to him.

660
00:46:11,893 --> 00:46:14,828
