we've got great news.

661
00:46:14,896 --> 00:46:15,828
Tell him.

662
00:46:15,897 --> 00:46:17,831
There's a huge international shipment

663
00:46:17,899 --> 00:46:18,957
coming through.

664
00:46:19,034 --> 00:46:22,492
We got the time, the place, the whole shebang.

665
00:46:22,570 --> 00:46:25,505
Well, what are we doing standing here then?

666
00:46:27,008 --> 00:46:28,942
How do you get this information?

667
00:46:29,010 --> 00:46:31,444
That's the second rule of police work.

668
00:46:31,513 --> 00:46:35,279
If you want to keep a secret,
don't tell the boss.

669
00:46:39,487 --> 00:46:42,923
You know he's making over $3 million a year?

670
00:46:42,991 --> 00:46:44,925
But he's paid no taxes.

671
00:46:44,993 --> 00:46:46,426
Nothing's in his name.

672
00:46:46,494 --> 00:46:49,429
If we can establish any payments to him,

673
00:46:49,497 --> 00:46:52,432
we can prosecute him for income tax evasion.

674
00:46:52,500 --> 00:46:53,432
What?

675
00:46:53,501 --> 00:46:55,935
I said we can prosecute him

676
00:46:56,004 --> 00:46:58,165
for income tax evasion.

677
00:46:58,239 --> 00:47:01,436
Try a murderer for not paying his taxes?

678
00:47:01,509 --> 00:47:03,500
Well, it's better than nothing.

679
00:47:05,313 --> 00:47:09,977
All right. How do we link him to the money?

680
00:47:10,051 --> 00:47:11,518
I don't know.

681
00:47:14,022 --> 00:47:15,853
Go to sleep, Oscar.

682
00:48:03,092 --> 00:48:04,889
A convoy of 5 to 10 trucks

683
00:48:04,960 --> 00:48:06,393
filled with Canadian whiskey

684
00:48:06,462 --> 00:48:09,898
