Canadian side of the bridge,

695
00:48:35,391 --> 00:48:37,325
thus surprising from the rear,

696
00:48:37,393 --> 00:48:40,556
and surprise, Mr. Ness, is half the battle.

697
00:48:40,629 --> 00:48:43,723
Yes, surprise is half the battle.

698
00:48:43,799 --> 00:48:46,199
Many things are half the battle.

699
00:48:46,268 --> 00:48:49,704
Let's think about what is all the battle.

700
00:48:49,772 --> 00:48:53,003
Let's take the fight to them, gentlemen!

701
00:48:53,075 --> 00:48:54,565
Thank you, Captain.

702
00:48:56,912 --> 00:48:58,709
All right.

703
00:48:58,781 --> 00:49:00,442
Move out.

704
00:49:17,433 --> 00:49:18,900
Take it easy.

705
00:49:21,036 --> 00:49:22,469
Take it easy.

706
00:49:22,538 --> 00:49:25,598
It'll all happen in time, hmm?

707
00:49:25,674 --> 00:49:27,505
This is the job.

708
00:49:27,576 --> 00:49:30,010
Don't wait for it to happen.

709
00:49:30,079 --> 00:49:32,513
Don't even want it to happen.

710
00:49:32,581 --> 00:49:35,175
Just watch what does happen.

711
00:49:36,619 --> 00:49:38,052
Are you my tutor?

