1388
01:39:24,355 --> 01:39:26,619
I got a permit for that.

1389
01:39:26,691 --> 01:39:28,124
Fine. Let's see it.

1390
01:39:29,761 --> 01:39:32,696
You know, I'm not the one under indictment.

1391
01:39:32,764 --> 01:39:34,197
Everything on the table.

1392
01:39:37,568 --> 01:39:39,331
Give him his gun back.

1393
01:39:39,404 --> 01:39:40,666
"To whom it may concern...

1394
01:39:40,738 --> 01:39:43,730
"Please extend to the bearer, Mr. Frank Nitti,

1395
01:39:43,808 --> 01:39:45,742
"all possible courtesy and consideration.

1396
01:39:45,810 --> 01:39:48,745
William Thompson, mayor of the city of Chicago."

1397
01:39:48,813 --> 01:39:50,110
I'm sorry, Mr. Ness.

1398
01:39:50,181 --> 01:39:52,115
You'll have to give it back.

1399
01:39:52,183 --> 01:39:53,275
Fine.

1400
01:39:53,351 --> 01:39:57,117
But that man does not go
back into that courtroom.

1401
01:39:57,188 --> 01:39:58,621
Do you understand me?

1402
01:39:58,690 --> 01:39:59,622
Yes, sir.

1403
01:40:29,320 --> 01:40:30,582
1634 Racine.

1404
01:40:30,655 --> 01:40:35,092
You know, I used to have
a friend who lived there.

1405
01:40:48,406 --> 01:40:50,340
Don't.

1406
01:40:50,408 --> 01:40:51,841
Let him go.

1407
01:40:55,580 --> 01:40:56,740
No!

1408
01:40:56,814 --> 01:40:58,247
Here. Take it.

1409
01:41:20,505 --> 01:41:22,439
[Gunshots]

1410
01:41:55,773 --> 01:41:56,899
Aah!

1411
01:45:08,332 --> 01:45:11,495
Here I am, Treasury man.

1412
01:45:11,569 --> 01:45:13,002
Come on.

1413
01:45:13,070 --> 01:45:15,004
Arrest me.

1414
01:45:15,072 --> 01:45:17,540
What are you waiting for?

1415
01:45:18,676 --> 01:45:21,736
Don't just stand there.
Arrest me.

1416
01:45:25,816 --> 01:45:27,681
Don't push me.

1417
01:45:30,287 --> 01:45:32,050
They're going to burn you.

1418
01:45:32,123 --> 01:45:33,090
Yeah?

1419
01:45:33,157 --> 01:45:37,059
I'll come see you burn, you son of a bitch,

1420
01:45:37,128 --> 01:45:39,688
'cause you killed my friend.

1421
01:45:39,764 --> 01:45:41,664
He died like a pig.

1422
01:45:41,732 --> 01:45:43,097
What did you say?

1423
01:45:43,167 --> 01:45:45,601
I said your friend died screaming

1424
01:45:45,670 --> 01:45:47,570
like a stuck Irish pig.

1425
01:45:47,638 --> 01:45:51,074
You think about that when I beat the rap.

1426
01:45:58,015 --> 01:45:59,812
Hey.

1427
01:45:59,884 --> 01:46:01,078
Aah!

1428
01:46:01,152 --> 01:46:04,349
Aah!

1429
01:46:04,422 --> 01:46:06,617
Did he sound anything like that?

1430
01:46:37,811 --> 01:46:40,245
One picture.
Come on. One picture.

1431
01:46:43,117 --> 01:46:46,052
Mr. Ness, take a look at this.

1432
01:46:47,588 --> 01:46:48,577
Mr. Ness.

1433
01:46:50,758 --> 01:46:52,692
Mr. Ness, you doing O.K.?

1434
01:46:52,760 --> 01:46:55,058
I think you better see this.

1435
01:46:55,129 --> 01:46:56,562
What is it?

1436
01:46:56,630 --> 01:46:59,929
What is it? That's a jury list, Mr. Ness.

1437
01:47:00,000 --> 01:47:01,433
They've been bribed.

1438
01:47:01,502 --> 01:47:03,868
Got it out of Nitti's coat.

1439
01:47:03,938 --> 01:47:05,371
Where is Nitti?

1440
01:47:07,374 --> 01:47:08,807
He's in the car.

1441
01:47:28,262 --> 01:47:30,355
This constitutes no evidence.

1442
01:47:30,431 --> 01:47:31,420
It has no providence.

1443
01:47:31,498 --> 01:47:34,433
Your Honor, the truth of the case

1444
01:47:34,501 --> 01:47:38,437
is that Capone is a killer and will go free.

1445
01:47:38,505 --> 01:47:41,440
The only way to deal with such men

1446
01:47:41,508 --> 01:47:42,941
is hunt them down.

1447
01:47:43,010 --> 01:47:44,443
I have forsworn myself.

1448
01:47:44,511 --> 01:47:47,947
I have broken every law I swore to defend.

1449
01:47:48,015 --> 01:47:49,812
I'm content I've done right.

1450
01:47:49,883 --> 01:47:52,716
That man must be stopped, and you must...

1451
01:47:52,786 --> 01:47:54,151
I'll be the judge

1452
01:47:54,221 --> 01:47:57,156
of what I must do, Mr. Ness.

1453
01:48:05,799 --> 01:48:07,699
Would you excuse us?

1454
01:49:10,297 --> 01:49:11,321
Bailiff.

1455
01:49:11,398 --> 01:49:12,365
Yes, sir?

1456
01:49:17,204 --> 01:49:20,037
Bailiff, go next door to Judge Hoffman's court.

1457
01:49:20,107 --> 01:49:22,871
They've just begun hearing a divorce action.

1458
01:49:22,943 --> 01:49:25,571
I want you to bring that jury in here

1459
01:49:25,646 --> 01:49:28,706
and take this jury to his court.

1460
01:49:30,484 --> 01:49:32,645
Bailiff, are those instructions clear?

1461
01:49:32,720 --> 01:49:34,153
Yes, sir.
They're clear.

1462
01:49:38,425 --> 01:49:42,088
Bailiff, I want you to switch the juries.

1463
01:49:42,162 --> 01:49:44,426
Your Honor, I object.

1464
01:49:45,699 --> 01:49:46,723
Overruled.

1465
01:49:51,572 --> 01:49:53,540
What did you tell him?

1466
01:49:54,775 --> 01:49:58,802
I told him his name was in the ledger, too.

1467
01:49:58,879 --> 01:50:01,677
His name wasn't in the ledger.

1468
01:50:03,117 --> 01:50:06,280
Wait. What is this?
Is this the law?

1469
01:50:06,353 --> 01:50:07,547
You're out of order.

1470
01:50:07,621 --> 01:50:08,883
I think that we...

1471
01:50:08,956 --> 01:50:11,550
I don't care what you think.

1472
01:50:11,625 --> 01:50:14,355
What do I look like?
Do something.

1473
01:50:14,428 --> 01:50:15,395
Order!

1474
01:50:17,097 --> 01:50:18,086
Your Honor,

1475
01:50:18,165 --> 01:50:21,259
we'd like to withdraw our plea of not guilty

1476
01:50:21,335 --> 01:50:24,133
and enter a plea of guilty.

1477
01:50:27,341 --> 01:50:29,002
Guilty?

1478
01:50:29,076 --> 01:50:30,805
Order in the court!

1479
01:50:30,878 --> 01:50:31,845
Order!

1480
01:50:33,547 --> 01:50:36,141
Guilty?

1481
01:50:36,216 --> 01:50:37,683
I'll give you guilty.

1482
01:50:41,221 --> 01:50:42,381
Bailiff!

1483
01:50:44,258 --> 01:50:46,351
Bailiff, clear the courtroom!

1484
01:50:50,430 --> 01:50:53,661
Your Honor. Your Honor, is that justice?

1485
01:50:53,734 --> 01:50:56,726
Why did he switch the jury?

1486
01:50:56,804 --> 01:50:59,364
Are you going to continue
going after the organization?

1487
01:50:59,439 --> 01:51:00,929
Excuse me.

1488
01:51:01,008 --> 01:51:05,502
I'm asking Your Honor, is this justice?

1489
01:51:05,579 --> 01:51:07,638
What about justice?

1490
01:51:09,516 --> 01:51:11,507
Is this justice?

1491
01:51:11,585 --> 01:51:13,485
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1492
01:51:15,022 --> 01:51:18,856
Never stop. Never stop fighting
till the fight is done.

1493
01:51:18,926 --> 01:51:20,484
What did you say?

1494
01:51:20,561 --> 01:51:23,826
Never stop fighting till the fight is done.

1495
01:51:23,897 --> 01:51:24,829
What?

1496
01:51:24,898 --> 01:51:26,263
You heard me, Capone.

1497
01:51:26,333 --> 01:51:28,858
You're nothing but talk and a badge.

1498
01:51:28,936 --> 01:51:30,460
Here endeth the lesson.

1499
01:51:30,537 --> 01:51:34,633
You're nothing but a lot of talk and a badge!

1500
01:51:34,708 --> 01:51:37,905
You're nothing but a lot of talk and a badge!

1501
01:52:57,591 --> 01:52:59,786
So much violence.

1502
01:54:05,392 --> 01:54:07,053
Cleaning up a little.

1503
01:54:17,371 --> 01:54:19,339
I guess it's goodbye.

1504
01:54:21,175 --> 01:54:22,938
Goodbye, George.

1505
01:54:25,512 --> 01:54:29,141
I want to, uh, thank you for this.

1506
01:54:29,216 --> 01:54:31,582
No. Thank you.

1507
01:54:47,501 --> 01:54:48,900
Mr. Ness...

1508
01:54:48,969 --> 01:54:51,369
I think he wanted you to have that.

1509
01:54:51,438 --> 01:54:53,906
He'd have wanted a cop to have it.

1510
01:54:58,712 --> 01:55:00,145
I'm going home.

1511
01:55:12,092 --> 01:55:14,390
Mr. Ness, any comment for the record?

1512
01:55:14,461 --> 01:55:17,396
The man who put Al Capone on the spot.

1513
01:55:17,464 --> 01:55:21,127
I happened to be there when the wheel went round.

1514
01:55:21,201 --> 01:55:23,465
They say they're going to repeal prohibition.

1515
01:55:23,537 --> 01:55:25,971
What will you do then?

1516
01:55:27,307 --> 01:55:28,706
I think I'll have a drink.

